<item>
            <title>[FELIX-1997] Actual configuration might not be reflected in the web console</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-1997</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If no configuration exists in the config admin, a default configuration is used which is derived from framework properties.&lt;br/&gt;
If these properties do not match the default settings, than the configuration view in the web console shows the wrong default settings - and not the &lt;br/&gt;
settings that are currently used.&lt;br/&gt;
One possible solution to fix this might be to create a configuration if the framework properties do not match the default settings&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
